<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>Crag: Corin Road Bouldering </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>Area: Cantaloupe Hill </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 **Memories (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Just enough holds for an ascent.  Hard work getting off the ground, a big move to the next incut, then you're on the slab and away.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V7 Project 2 - open (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Technical and gut-busting.  Grade is a guess.  Some seriously strenuous layback moves.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 Slab proj (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Left side of the slab.  Delicate!  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47627845000" lon="148.93187345000">
    <name>Boulder: Glitz Rock </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 Without Words (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start in the vague scoop and grovel your way to a desperate mantle. Not great.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 *Tally Ho (2.4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at the spike (same start as Vendetta). Straight up via the corner/groove.  Quite messy after it's rained.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V7 ***Vendetta (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at Tally Ho, then follow the break rightwards to the rounded arête, then mantle/rock over to the top. Progressively crimpier with thinner feet. Part of the crux footer has broken off, now a bit harder (Sept 2023).
[ :video_camera: Chris Beers](https://www.instagram.com/p/B0Mc3kADFQ-/)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V11 ***Cerebro (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start for Vendetta, then drop down into the underclings, make some hard moves through underclings and slopers finishing out the top of the boulder (as for Vendetta or the Joker).

[ :video_camera: CMCC](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yIni8Cbw_3U)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 *Contempt Left (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ As per Contempt, but topout for Tally Ho.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V6 *Contempt (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on the far left side of the underclings (just right of the start to Tally Ho), then straight up, topping out right of where Tally Ho tops out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 **Dripping on Trips Left (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start at the big underclings, make a big move into the horizontal break and then traverse left to finish as for Tally Ho.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V6 **Dripping on Trips (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on the big underclings and head to the crimpy rail for Vendetta and top out as for Vendetta.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V6 ***The Joker (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ A Canberra classic - the proud line diagonally up the front of the boulder as you approach on the walk in.  Good positive holds, but still hard work!  Note: this is a *squat start* - you start on the first set of good holds.

[ :video_camera: CMCC](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I1PHSscbv1I)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V7 ***The Joker - Sit (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The full sit start to the Joker.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V9 **Stopping All Stations (8m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start up The Joker, then reverse Vendetta, and finish up Tally Ho.

Not as contrived as it sounds - actually a pretty nice line. The Vendetta rail is harder in this direction.

Gets V9 in the guidebook, but might be a bit soft.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V9 **Stopping Absolutely All Stations (8m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The full link-up of the boulder. Stopping All Stations with the sit start.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V9/10 ***Stop with the Stopping Stations </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start the Joker, climb this, then reverse Vendetta and finish up the fingery mantle of Contempt. Sustained and consistently hard.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V10 **Derailment </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start the Joker and then when the diagonal crack runs out make hard moves to reverse Cerebro finishing up Tally Ho.

[ :video_camera: CMCC](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UpCU8i9MS-c)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V10 **Lipstick Lesbian (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start for the Joker, then head straight up where the rock splits into two cracks. Long dyno to the big slope, match then mantel up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0 Persian Rug (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Nice warmup problem upslope and behind Glitz Rock  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0 Number 5 (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Right hand variant to Persian Rug (#6 in CCA guide).  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0 - 1 Prydain (2.5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start left of persian rug on the undercling and up the &quot;arete&quot;.  Eliminate - left side rail is out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588995000" lon="148.93166635000">
    <name>Boulder: Prow Rock </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 *Intrusion (2.5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start problem through obvious basalt or similar intrusion on back of boulder and right of prow.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2/3 *Intrusion stand (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand variant to intrusion.  Very height-dependent.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 *Ruffian (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start and then go diagonally left up the seam.  Falling at the end would be bad.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V5 ***Spruce Moose - stand (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Standing start to Spruce Moose - slap up the boulder.  Burly.
[ :video_camera: CMCC](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HXjpYVOjOjw)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V8 ***Spruce Moose - sitstart (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start down on the left arete then slap out to the right side of the prow then continue up with big compression moves up the prow.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V8 Lanky Yanky (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Up and left crimping under roof then up and over.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 Throw Back (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Long throw to crimp.   ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 Pubs (2.5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The slab.   ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47577625000" lon="148.93144070000">
    <name>Area: Slab Rock </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V1 Another (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Grunt your way up the slab on the left side right in the trees.  If you can be bothered.  You might get a real surprise if you fall.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 *Szady Slap (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Traverse all the way along the slab from the right hand side of the rock as you come uphill.  Hope you've got good friction in your hands!  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V1 Peter Pan (2.5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Left of the start to Szady Slap, take a run at the slab, jump, get your feet set and reach for glory.  Invigorating cooldown.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47621950000" lon="148.93150105000">
    <name>Boulder: Number 15 boulder </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 **Back in Black (#15) (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from left of slab then traverse right and up the slab on crimps.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 **Slow and Low (#16) (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit-start traverse the boulder left to right.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 Bergs (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit-start the arete.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47634960000" lon="148.93124620000">
    <name>Boulder: Heart Block(s) </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 Little Arete (#18) (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit-start and up to the left or the right.  Rock on the left of the track just before heart block  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 **Drug Money for the Bunny (#19) (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Access is along forestry roads, which in most cases seem to have been closed and gated.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V6 *Organs in Orbit (#20) (10m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Traverse left to right then up, finishing as for 22, the righthandmost climb.  Either gaston through the crux or execute a hard cross-through.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V7 Vena Cava </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ start left of rocks on undercling. continue up underclings to the break and straight up 'check your head'  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 ***Check Your Head (#21) (8m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ classic Highball.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V5 **Right Ventricle </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on the crack and stay in crack then finish up and right. V5  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V6 **Swinging Doors (#22) (6m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Up onto a good flat edge with crappy footers, get yourself set, dyno out left then up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47634960000" lon="148.93124620000">
    <name>V0 Project 1 (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The crack.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47634960000" lon="148.93124620000">
    <name>V3 Vitruvian (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start at flake, matching hands above.  Layback from there out to the edge of the slope, cut feet, find the slot and up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47634960000" lon="148.93124620000">
    <name>V5 **Visceral (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start as for Vitruvian, layback out right, cut feet and dangle in thin air, then turn and heel hook up in the slot just before the end of the jutting prow.  V4 moves up to here...  Now execute a gut-wrenching mantle with your left foot dangling in the air.  Positive holds.  Pretty damn contrived.  On reflection, it's not worth stars, but it's fun to try and mantel over the shit foot-slot.  The full line is the real prize.  Don't touch the ground, obviously!  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47634960000" lon="148.93124620000">
    <name>V9 Project 1 - prow traverse (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Traverse from the start of Vitruvian right around the boulder, heel hooking and groaning all the way.  Pretty much a huge campus problem really.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47634960000" lon="148.93124620000">
    <name> Project 2 - the Cave (Boulder 2.5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start inside the cave, move to a downward-sloped rail, huge throw up to next hold.  Not sure if it's possible without hitting the rock behind, but this is one for the insanely strong.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 Number 23 </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit-start.  Looks like something has broken, as this has minimal hand holds and small feet.  Looked to be a single dynamic move to the top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47621878014" lon="148.92999565949">
    <name>Sector: The Upper Ridge </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V1 *Number 1 (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 *Jayenne (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start from the bottom of the boulder.  After gaining your feet, a fair sized dynamic move out left from smears will get you to the glory rail, and then finish as for #1.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0 Number 2 (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Access is along forestry roads, which in most cases seem to have been closed and gated.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V1 *Nice Guys Finish Last (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Slab.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V7 **O'Ren Ishi </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.  Traverse left then up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 **Cotten Mouth (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start then over onto slab.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V6 **Rumspringa (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit-start up the arete.  Quite overhung.  A great quality climb well worth the walk up to this sector just by itself.  Low in the grade.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V7 **Fraud Landis </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start then traverse left onto slopes from Rumspringa.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V5 **Rumspringa stand (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Seems about the same as Rumspringa as the crux balance move is in the stand, but doesn't include the heel hook above the head.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V6 *QJ WIN </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Crimp and dyno. vertical problem just 5m down from 'snatch strap'  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 *Snatch Strap (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start right side then up the curving line  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 *Boat Mantle (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 South Paw </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ sit start bottom left climb right  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V1 *Blue Jeans (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit-start then mantle.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 **More moss </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name> big arete (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ climbed?  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V7 ***Blood Makes Noise (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start with hand jam between blocks then into crack, pull lip and up right. Epic line!  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V8 ***Scream </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start with a hand jam between blocks and then into crack, head straight up and dyno.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 Between the lines </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ start on flakes up and exit right with tiny crimps  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 Counter point </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ right arete  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0 Corner Bloc </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Access is along forestry roads, which in most cases seem to have been closed and gated.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 **Reality Creep (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ sit start then to jug and slab out  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47719632736" lon="148.92989033393">
    <name>Area: Sundries </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 Dren </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start, grabbing either side of the prow.  Work your way up and top out - average feet all the way.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 Soot </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Layback the flake to the left up onto the boulder, then top out to the right.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 Rarze </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.  Up to the top of the first boulder, then head straight up and slightly left over the second.  Once on top, downclimb round to the left.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 Tauris </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start as per #3.  Once at the top of the first boulder, follow the seam up and right.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name> Flicking your switch (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ In front of problems 3 and 4, accessed under the huge burnt tree.  Difficult and blank looking layback up and left to a tricky top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0 *Chime </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.  Up the broken corner using many different features.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V5 ***Its daddy you shit head </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start round to the right.  Follow the good layback flake up and left round the tock, and top out straight up once at the 'ledge'.  Downclimb over the back.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 *Dance for daddy </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Mantle up, starting off the block.  Awkward ledge, then top out straight up.  Downclimb off the back.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47774146944" lon="148.92888485800">
    <name>Area: The Ice Blocks </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0 More </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.  Up crack in corner, trending right and round onto the top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.477682" lon="148.928839">
    <name>V4 **Born-again Hooligan (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start up to a big sloper then up to a good edge on top.  Easy top out and down climb. GPS (approx): -35.477682, 148.928839  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V5 Crete it </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start then up left, staying on the main block (don't escape up the crack between the boulders).  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 Skullduggery </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start as per #3.  Big throw right to a jug, then up to the top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.477682" lon="148.928839">
    <name>V7 ***Aspen Armor </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Hard sit start up to break, then head up ledges to top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.477682" lon="148.928839">
    <name>V10 ***Skills to Pay the Bills </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start as per #5 to break, then traverse right on slopers to the end of the break, then head up to top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 *Stone Cutter </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Boulder down and left of Aspen arbor.   Start at the bottom right of the broken circle,  move left to the arete and up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V5 Price Check </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start up the arete, then top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47693455000" lon="148.92745645000">
    <name>Area: Lost World </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V6 ***One Undisclosed Period in Paradise (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ A solid walk for a decent problem. Sit start on obvious large flat flake to high but easy top out. To get off the top, move left and jump off onto mats.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name> Egg Project (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Squat start from low diagonal undercling holds (forms an acute upside down triangle). Big pull to sloper on the lip followed by a big tension move out left to the positive arete and an easy top. Will be all time when it goes. Likely double digits.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name> Lip Project (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Left to right rising lip traverse.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47484235237" lon="148.93394256940">
    <name>Boulder: The Hand </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 **Cute Kill (6m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from the cave up holding onto a big flake.  Compressive move to start.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V4 *Pinky Cling (6m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Contrived sit start.  6 metres, but an easy terrain crack up top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0 Kerl (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Straight up a mossy crack.  Nothing difficult.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V1 *Thumb Mantle (1.8m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start. Good mantle practice. **This problem no longer exists as the entire shield that comprised it has toppled over. Geologic time includes now.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0 Middle Finger (5.5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Up the right side of the palm.  Easy terrain.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V5 *Tickler (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.  The hardest V3 in the entire world?  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V2 *Skin end (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Up the side of the boulder using layback-type moves.  Hard work to get your feet on top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0 #7 RH variant (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Good warmup for the burlier #6-7.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V1 Divagation (2.5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ It really is a word.  Sit start at the opening of the cave around the corner and uphill a few metres from #7.  Start on positive holds, then find the hidden hold up high to progress.  The boulder behind is in - it's a cross between a chimney climb and a face climb!  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V0- Mellifluous (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Small boulder on the way in to the hand.  Warm-up sit start.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47588431812" lon="148.92812416718">
    <name>V3 *Trichiasis (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start for the V3, then exit out the roof and up the vertical slab.  Direct might be a fair bit harder if you're willing to huck a huge dyno - not sure it's viable.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 Number 24 </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Access is along forestry roads, which in most cases seem to have been closed and gated.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.46767052692" lon="148.95771391891">
    <name>Boulder: George's Boulder </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 **Call Girls (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start to the far right low down, then pull around the corner.  Finish with higher traverse to jug. The warm up...  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V5 **On Hold (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start to the far right and pull around the corner.  Finish with lower traverse/slopes to jug. Desperate.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V6 **The Tower (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start and up the arete.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 **FIS (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start and straight up the thin slab  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 **JAS (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start on the rail and up through a few sidepulls and crimps to a slab topout  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 *Shy moves (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Up and onto the slab.  Smearing moves and a few check your head moments.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V6 **Slopesanity (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Reverse 1a/b from the start of the rail past the victory jugs, using only the slopers.  Arguably better than 1a, slightly more fun moves in the opposite direction.  Holds all face the wrong way to traverse in this direction though, so it's like downclimbing slopers!  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V6 **Leg Spinner (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start to good jug, then up to good edge (dyno or intermediate crimps) and up.  A very sizeable dyno if you do it that way - bring a few mats to stack if you love your ankles.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V10 ***Shape Shifters (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Straight up the front side of the boulder just before the end of Phone Sex. Sit start to big jug, heal hook and big chuck to crimp out left. pull hard to the high gaston and up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name> Foreign Correspondent (Boulder 5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ As for 'Shape Shifters' but gain the crimp with a right hand and go left up the vague arete.

No proposed grade but &quot;Double digits for sure&quot;

[ :camera: D Fisher](https://www.instagram.com/p/DMRIA02zCsQ)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V5 **Happy ending (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start as for Shape Shifters. Up to the jugs then right along the rail to join Shy Moves, then continue right and up the slab to top out.

[ :video_camera: CMCC](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9xeq4LKZ5Do)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V7 **Phone Diddle (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The start many people use when claiming 'Phone Sex'!  From the scooped out area on the far side of the boulder as you walk in, start one block right on larger holds and then traverse out right to the jug for 1a/1b.  Still has the hardest moves of 'Phone Sex', but the full sit is now doable as the start has been cleaned up.  Requires less endurance than the full line.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V8 **Phone Sex (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start from the scooped out area on the far side of the boulder on low slopers, hard start moves out right on crimps (You may need to clean the Blackberries as they are persistent).  Many have started one block over for the sit-start, taking out the most strenuous moves of the climbs - see 'Phone Diddle'.  Traverse out right and end on the jug for 1a/1b.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V8 **Phone Sex with a Happy Ending (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start at Phone Sex and continue up Happy Ending to end on top of the boulder. 

Nicer end to Phone Sex but not much harder.

May have been climbed before (if so, feel free to claim it!).  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V11 Blood Moon (5.5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start as for Phone Sex and finish through Shape Shifters.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V12 ***Mitosis (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The impossible line directly above the Phone Diddle start. Sit start at the ledge, move to some tiny crimps then up through some imaginary slopers to top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V9 ***Phone Extension (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start from the sit start on phone sex, reach the finish jug of that problem but get set up, head into the 'Leg Spinner' dyno and topout.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V9 *Full Traverse (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Traverse the full boulder.  One for the pumpers.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V8 Reverse Charges (1m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Reverse 'Phone Sex'.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 *Dialed (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Up the flake at the right side of the boulder as you approach it from the parking area (flake's gone so this problem is either way more difficult or just not worth the trouble).  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V8/9 *My Toe Cyst </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Do Phone Sex then keep traversing through reverse Call Girls until you reach the base of The Tower then do The Tower.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>Area: Snake Rock Boulders </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47536905000" lon="148.95220905000">
    <name>Sector: Roadside Boulders </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 1. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start left arete, climb straight up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V3 2. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start left arete, climb straight up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V1 3. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start right arete, climb straight up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>VB 4. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from bottom of crack, climb crack and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V3 *5. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start right arete, climb up and top out (boulder to left out).  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V6 Bart Sendy (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start of 5. Start with your left hand on the left arete and right hand on the obvious side pull.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V0 6. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start from bottom of slab, climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V6 *The Nipple Mantle (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start matched on rounded hold at end of horizontal block. Mantle block (opposing boulder out).  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V5 **The Nipple Traverse (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start matched on rounded hold at end of horizontal block. Traverse rightwards finishing as for route 7.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V7 **The Nipple (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at base of boulder beneath roof (opposing boulder out). Climb up, traverse leftwards along roof and finish as for &quot;The Nipple Mantle&quot;.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V4 **7. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at base of boulder beneath roof (opposing boulder out). Climb straight up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 *8. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start right side of the arete, climb straight up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V5 **9. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start right side of the arete, climb straight up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 *10. (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from base of left hand crack. Climb leftwards onto slab then straight up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V1 11. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from base of left hand crack, climb crack and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V0 *12. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from base of right hand boulder, climb arete/crack and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V4 *I'm Not Your Bitch Stand (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start, climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V9 **I'm Not Your Bitch (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from base of boulder. Climb up following seam topping out at its highset point.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V6 13. (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from base of boulder (leftside). Climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47762325000" lon="148.95249740000">
    <name>Boulder: Riverside Boulder </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 *1. (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start right arete, climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V1 2. (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start large rail, climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V3 *3. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start base of crack, climb up and top top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V3 *4. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from base of prow, climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V0 *5. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from large flake. Climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47796720000" lon="148.95252755000">
    <name>Boulder: Cartman Boulder </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V5 *1. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V3 *2. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V6 **The Summer of Nath (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V4 *3. (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start from base of arete. Climb arete and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V9 *Sweets (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V3 *4. (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V5 Ruth (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start from base of arete. Climb arete and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V4 ***Clementine (6m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start from base of flake. Climb flake and top out. Classic. One of the best at this grade in Canberra!  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V7 **5. (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from base of flake. Climb flake and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V4 Duffy St (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V4 6. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 *7. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V1 8. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start from base of corner. Climb corner and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
