    <name>V4 10. (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47818385000" lon="148.95256490000">
    <name>Boulder: Ike Boulder </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V1 1. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 *2. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start (left of arete) on rail. Climb face\arete and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V1 3. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start corner, climb corner and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V5 4. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start undercut arete, climb arete and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V0 5. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start rounded arete, climb arete and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>VB 6. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 7. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start then climb up and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V1 *8. (6m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start then traverse left across face finishing as for rounded arete.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V4 *The Great Speed Climbing Debate (7m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at the left of the boulder and traverse right (staying off the top) until the right arête, then top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47826755000" lon="148.95230830000">
    <name>Boulder: Trackside Boulder </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V1 1. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from slot, climb onto back of boulder and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V4 **2. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from slot, climb right arete and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V7 **3. (8m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from slot, traverse across prow, then across face at 45 degree angle topping out as for left arete.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V8/9 *Bev, Bath &amp; Beyond (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Linking the V6 sitstart into Frankenruby to add a bit of spice  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V8 ***FrankenRuby (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from slot at base of corner, climb prow and top out.

[ :video_camera: Bevan Ashby](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZKfbnn3v6wo)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V4 **4. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from slot at base of corner, climb corner and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V6 **Jerk's Variant (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at base of corner, climb left through corner and then across arete at 45 degree angle topping out as for left arete. Similar difficulty to 6.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V5 **5. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from left side pull, climb into corner and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V6 **6. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start from left side pull, then across face at 45 degree angle topping out as for left arete.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V8 *The Lanky Imp (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at base of corner, climb left through corner but stay low and go directly from the big jug to the left arete, then climb arete/face and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V3 *7. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start left arete, climb arete/face and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name> Project (Boulder 4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start left arete, climb arete/face and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 *8. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on edges, climb face then top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 *9. (6m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on edges, traverse across face at 45 degree angle topping out as for left arete.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 *10. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on edges, climb face then top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V0 11. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start at base of arete, climb arete and top out (this route is also the best decent).  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V1 *12. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start middle of wall, climb face and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V2 13. (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start about 2m right of left arete, climb left onto arete and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V3 *14. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start at base of arete, climb arete and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V3 15. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start about 2m left of arete, climb sloping holds and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V0 16. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start at base of corner, climb corner and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.47637228984" lon="148.95234975572">
    <name>V1 17. (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start about 2m left of corner, climb face and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.49448245000" lon="148.92632220000">
    <name>Field: Strawberry Fields </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V12 ***Slim Pickings </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start from left hand crimp and low right hand undercling, up prow to insecure top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V8 **Ringo Starr (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on the face with a left hand crimp, right hand side pull and climb straight up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V11 **Snakes and Ladders (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on high crimps and follow line of small crimps to the top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V12 **Snakes and Ladders Right (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start as for Snakes and Ladders, instead of going right hand to the crimp, cross over with the left and head out to the arete on the right to set up for a committing move to the lip.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V7 **Icarus (1m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start to Snakes and Ladders from high crimp.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V6 *Gruntled (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on thin horizontal crimp and head straight up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V7 **Talos (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on good low edge and traverse right on small crimps to top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V1 *Traverse </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start at bottom of feature and follow juggy rising  traverse up the arete.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 **Atonia (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The obvious crack in gully  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 **Corinthian (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start hand crack in gully. Span out right up finger crack on poor feet  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 The Green Sheep </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on crimps, slap the top, and mantle.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 Jump! </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start, jump to the arete, mantle, slab to the top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 Mum Duties </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Step left onto the slab from the blocks, traverse left to the arete, then up the slab to the top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 Moss-berries (3.5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on slopy lip then mantle the corner and climb up the mossy slab. Don't brush the moss off for extra top out fun.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V6 **Achilles heel (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sitstart by slots underneath huge flake, up and mantle the corner.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 **Call Me Right (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sitstart the middle of face on jug. Up then trend rightward to mantle.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V5 *Open Book (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sitstart the middle of face on jug. Straight up and mantle into groove.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name> 4 (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Unknown name/ grade. Something goes up the middle, unsure if it starts on the left or right.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V7 **Hot Sake (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start and move left onto slab via long move.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V7 *Cold Sake </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Low, left start to Hot Sake.
Sit start with a good right crimp and a bad left sloper, up the sloper rail and along this to finish as for Hot Sake.
A little bit morpho, probably easier if you're tall, harder if you're short.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 *Vertical Life Magazine (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start. Deadpoint to crimp rail and then balance top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V11 *The Two Lives </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sweet compression bloc  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V9 *Strong Frenchy (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start on high opposing side-pulls and move straight up. Non-giants might need to stack pads to reach the start holds. First sent by a strong visiting French guy.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V8 Weak Kiwi (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start as for Strong Frenchy but bail out left at the top. Easier, and probably not as nice as that climb.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 *Spring Edition 2019 (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start with left hand sharp crimp and right hand sloper (detached block at base is out). Funky moves with bad feat lead to a tricky top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V7 *Tiny pocket of doom </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start sitting on the rock matches on good crimp, make you way up past the bulge, hopefully your good enough to avoid the tiny pocket of doom.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 Tiny Slab Of Doom </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start the slab just up and right from 'Tiny Pocket Of Doom'. Crimp, smear and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V1 Big Flake </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start on the big juggy flake, and up. Probably done before, just adding it as it was fun enough, and a good one for little kids.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 **The Queens Mantle (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on right crimp and slopey edge then climb up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V6 The Queens Mantle sit-start (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on the flake down and right, hard reach to join the stand.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 **Left mantle (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on the slopey top edge then climb up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 Cabbage </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand on obvious ledge straight up using left sidepull and small crimps.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V1 *Give it a crack (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at crack and climb up. Wobbly pillar is in however it might come loose sometime.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 **Wabi-sabi (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start and up good crimps on the mossy face  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 Fumei (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start, right hand on vague arete, left on whatever you can find and up  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V10 **Split System </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on big sloping feature and head up the seam. On the back arete of the big boulder above the main area.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 **Slabezoid (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start and up slab between two aretes.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 Slabezoid Sit (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Access is along forestry roads, which in most cases seem to have been closed and gated.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 **Zaglossus Beak (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start and compress up pointed face.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 *Low Baller </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start bottom left of the big rail. Traverse up and right to top out through decent slopey edges/crimps.

(Boulder is down the hill a little bit below Slim Pickings)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 *Crack warm up (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Layback the crack and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 **Ugg Thug (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand or jump start to good rail and continue up face to top out on good holds.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V6 *Another compression warmup </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start and climb the compression without using the left side of the crack  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V1 Another Crack Warmup (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start the crack and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 *Cutting Teeth </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on small compression make a few moves to the lip and scuttle back around the corner t top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V1 Chicken run </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on small crimps on the right side of the face and bail out up and right  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V5 **Preggers prog </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start as for Chicken Run, head left through crimps and exit in the middle of the face

[ :video_camera: Zoe ](https://youtu.be/YlKbYAc2PK4?si=5MOTt6jrUOP18BC_)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V6 Extended ediiton </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start as for chicken run, climb all the way right and top out the seam.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 **Undocumented (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start in the break and use arete and crimp on the face to top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.50386070763" lon="148.91980222198">
    <name>Field: The Passionate Ones </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V9 ***The Passionate Ones (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Crimpy highball face. Stack pads to reach the high right crimp and left foot. Crimps to arete then up to high topout. Watch the landing.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.50635721270" lon="148.92936380489">
    <name>Area: Asgard </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V1 Bifrost </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.
Easiest of the 4 problems on the Approach Boulder.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 **End Of Fimbulwinter </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 Bluetooth </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 Nimble Harold </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V5 ***Dark Befalls The Raven </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ One of the prettiest boulders around.

Stand start the big slab and straight up.

Probably v4/5? If you stack pads to get on easier, probably take a grade off.
You can also step onto the slab from the block on the left and top out at about v3.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 Word Of Wyrd </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start in the hole between Dark Befalls The Raven and the massive blocks in the middle of the sector.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V1 **Laidback Loki </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.
Crack on the left end of The Back Wall.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 **Ash Over Ice </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 Son Of A Trickster </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 Geri </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 Freki </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 ***The Huntsman </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start.
The easiest problem on the Project Boulder, also the easiest way off the boulder.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V5 The Huntress </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start as for the Huntsman but go left and up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V5 *Gnaw the root (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on opposing crimps and push to the top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name> Project #1 (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start at the low left undercling and right crimp, making your way directly to the crimp, then work your way up and left.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52721870706" lon="148.92393094547">
    <name>Field: The Outer Rim </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52303642751" lon="148.92455304692">
    <name>Area: Dathomir </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52542349872" lon="148.92553354053">
    <name>Area: Dagobah </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52542349872" lon="148.92553354053">
    <name> The Wall Project (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The very tall slabby face right in front of you as you walk up the tree root stairs. Partially cleaned.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52542349872" lon="148.92553354053">
    <name> The Blunt Arete Project (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The blunt arete right of ' The Wall Project', finishing as for 'The Ramp Project'.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52542349872" lon="148.92553354053">
    <name> The Ramp Project (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Up the obvious left leading ramp to a high finish.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52542349872" lon="148.92553354053">
    <name>V3 **Do, Or Do Not </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Mega classic moderate grade highball! Stand start and up the obvious flake to a high finish direct, or slightly right above the other blocks to the right if you want a less risky finish  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52687930727" lon="148.92553753471">
    <name>Area: The Asteroid Field </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52773736867" lon="148.92525263343">
    <name>Area: Hoth </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52721870706" lon="148.92393094547">
    <name>V3 **Slaygirls </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start with dishes on the face and bad footer, head straight up.
On the way to 'Defying Wampa', kinda of near the boundary of 'The Asteroid Field' and 'Hoth'.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52721870706" lon="148.92393094547">
    <name>V11 ***Defying Wampa </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start on the obvious sloper rail standing on the block on the ground, follow the rails uo and left to top out.
Absolute mega classic!  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52701428954" lon="148.92301850330">
    <name>Area: Endor </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52609209226" lon="148.92333604174">
    <name>Area: Mandalore </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52898393208" lon="148.92301335381">
    <name>Area: The Moons Of Lothal </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53009479721" lon="148.92253433064">
    <name>Area: Tatooine </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52721870706" lon="148.92393094547">
    <name>V6 ***Something Deeply Hidden </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start on the lowest horizontal rail and top out via the scoop.
Kind of deep around the back of the area.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52721870706" lon="148.92393094547">
    <name> Project (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Up the obvious fridge. Probably 4 or 5, was cleaned but not climbed on a wet day. Go for it.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52721870706" lon="148.92393094547">
    <name> Project (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ A mega amongst megas.
Down deep in the sector. Compression masterclass. Probably 14+.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52962410865" lon="148.92083822382">
    <name>Area: Dantooine </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52408845981" lon="148.89677883029">
    <name>Boulder: Kelvin Bloc </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 Fridge Lift (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start just left of the arete. Straight up to the arete, then follow it to the top  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 *Baby Stop It (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start 1m right of Turn the Sheets, straight up to the highest point of the boulder  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 *Turn the Sheets (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start 1m right of Payment, up on small holds to a tenuous rock over  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 **Payment (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on the lower arete and traverse right to finish between Fridge Lift and Baby Stop it  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 *Fridge Press (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at the lower arete and mantle onto slab  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V7 **Non-Zero Possibility (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on the arete left of Payment. Up to slopers then traverse left and up blunt arete  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V9 Tails of the Drift (8m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start as for 'Non Zero Possibility', but continue traversing to the left, finishing as for Kelvinator V6.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V8 Chasing Ghosts (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start below Erico, into layaway and up through slopes and pinch tending right. 

*Line on this one is approximate- seems like it may be quite contrived. If anyone has clarity on where this goes please edit the topo/ description.*  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V5 *Erico (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on slopers. Mantle on prayers  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 *Shut the Door (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start low on sidepull. Straight up through big move to a jug and mantle.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V6 *Kelvinator (6m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start as for Shut the Door. Traverse left staying low, and finish using the very large footer  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 Undercounter (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start. Proceed up on nice holds  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 Descent (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ On the right side of the face facing the road. Usually reversed.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 Hard Descent (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Slab and thin crack between descent and Fridge lift on the face near the road.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name>Crag: The Kelvin Field </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name>V5 Once Upon A Time in Namadgi (8m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on the furthest right hand side of the boulder on the large horizontal. Traverse it left, under the overlap and up on good holds.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name> Open Project (Boulder )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Start matched on the horizontal and climb up. A line I was going to do but ran out of time.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52488290271" lon="148.89740803583">
    <name>Boulder: Citadel Wall </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name>V4 **The Primis (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ First line done at the Field- or is it?! If not, write your lines up! Sit start on opposing sidepulls and move upwards through more opposing holds, trending left into huge gaston and then up to good slopes from where you can reach to the top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name>V3 **The Primis Direct (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ A direct finish to 'The Primis'. Start as for the Primus head directly up an mantle out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name>V5 *The Electric Skin Wizard (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start matched on the sloper on the right hand side of the boulder. Move to a good edge then make a big move to the sloping arete. Traverse the sloping arete left and top out as for The Primus. The edge you move to is a bit suspicious. It may break. Be careful as the fall isn't the best.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52514610209" lon="148.89739445734">
    <name>Boulder: Throne Boulder </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name>V0 Warm up slab (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ 3m Left of throne room lhs. Stand start and up trending slightly left. Watch the little rock pedestal when you're topping out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name>V4 **Throne room lhs (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ One for the folks that don't like chicken winging. Sit start at juggy block side pull with high feet for opposition. Up to finger jugs then move the feet onto the right side of the crack and pull into the original throne room and finish up that. If you don't like the sit start, the stand from the finger jugs is a nice V3.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name>V3 ***Throne Room (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at the back of the crack matched on the cracks undercling. Pull into the crack and climb it to the top. It isn't over until your standing on top of the boulder!.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name>V3 **Right-Hand Aide (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start jug on right boulder. Compress the good slopers and straight over the front. The boulder on the left is out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.52506428319" lon="148.89725006757">
    <name>V1 *Hoochie Coochie Spaceman </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start at the obvious hold in the lower middle of the boulder. Move up through side pulls and slopers to the victory jug and top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53084540000" lon="148.88815655000">
    <name>Field: Spark Boulders </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 **Triple Swell (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start in jug sidepull. Up the bulge features to committing but easy topout.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name> Seam project (Boulder 3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start then up using crack in left hand and some bad slopers for the right. v10+  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V4 *Jacques (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on round arete with good flake. Long move to crimp then techy mantle.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V7 ***Experiment 221 (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start in slot. Left then up the cracks with a big dyno.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V6 **Doormat (6m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start bottom right. Traverse left through jugs then a crimpy crux.

[ :video_camera: Stephen Waring ](https://youtu.be/DfwdgfAyIiA?si=Yl79GrI7CgiIeru8)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V8 *Doormat direct </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on two underling edges, make a couple moves to gain the horizontal break finish up doormat.

[ :video_camera: Stephen Waring](https://youtu.be/U7ytX2e4Dx8?si=qhj5FgKn7Bnxdfxc)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V3 *Spare key (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sharp compression boulder. Stand/crouch at the blunt arete with a left hand dish and right hand side pull flake. Could start from a sit on lower holds  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 *Doorbell (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Fun easy slab on the face to the left of spare key  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V9 **Lip Reader </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ sit start at the bottom of the seam make a large move to the lip and work your way into the scoop to top out.
[ :video_camera: Stephen ](https://youtu.be/_9XpTELNnoE?si=nPYcv9pu20Tvc0o6)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V8 Snakes in the Grass </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start bottom left of slopey crack. Traverse right to v2 mantle. Pumpy and painful.

[ :video_camera: Stephen ](https://youtu.be/NKGoungVx1c?si=cdTP3Yrkhb5nr0pu)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>Field: The Hideaway </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53300454403" lon="148.88086800123">
    <name>Field: Banana Hill Bouldering </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V1 **Over the Hedge (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on big undercling with detached footer. Traverse right following the crack and mantle at the end.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305" lon="148.88039">
    <name>V8 **Escape Room (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start matched on sloper and straight up through slopers and pinches. Once you get the crack join 'Over the Hedge' to topout.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V5 **Riddle Me This (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start as for 'Escape room' but traverse all the way right then up into shared topout.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53327" lon="148.88092">
    <name>V5 *Bushwhacked (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Double toe hook start with hands in low jug. Then up arete.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>VB Bellyflop Mantle (1m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Jump start to jugs then mantle.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53323" lon="148.88103">
    <name>V3 **Yankee Doodle (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start matched on jug then traverse left finishing matched around the corner on jug. Finishes where 'Microchasm' starts.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V5 **Battle toad </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start low on large shelf and make your up and over the blunt prow  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V1 *Mind the Gap Left (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start with undercling then left around the corner to easy topout.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V2 *Mind the Gap Middle (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start with undercling then straight up to slopey mantle.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V2 **Mind the Gap Right (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start with undercling then right through edges to mantle.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V6 *Cassinia (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on high undercling with very low feet. To good edge then right and topout.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V8 **Roscoe the Bear (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start on broken crimps. Straight up to a slopey mantle.

Upgraded from v7 due to a breakage.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V0 Ant Ridge (8m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Up the ridge left of 'High Voltage'  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5332" lon="148.88121">
    <name>V3 ***High Voltage (10m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Up through crease following it until it ends. Then carefully onto slab and scramble the rest of the way.

Inspection on a rope is a good idea.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53299" lon="148.8811">
    <name>V3 *Ziggurat (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start compressing good holds then onto jugs and traverse left all the way to the top.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53295" lon="148.88126">
    <name>V5 ***Fireball Dyno (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start with two good crimps and poor feet. Dyno to top then mantle.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V10 **Aerial Shooting (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start matched on flat crimp with poor feet. Traverse right on crimps to mantle.

[ :video_camera: Stephen Waring](https://youtube.com/shorts/1ynDtY5Ymoc?si=hMJ1u4h52Rn2w0kn)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V8 The Hog </name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on crimps on the bulge to the right of 'Aerial Shooting' and work your way up.

[ :video_camera: Stephen Waring](https://youtube.com/shorts/5H5_JC8SO7g?si=BdCToBM6nA78XkLZ)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53322012015" lon="148.88106165756">
    <name>Sector: Trad Climbing </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53315" lon="148.8811">
    <name>21 *Soup Dragon (10m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The curving off-width.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53323" lon="148.88103">
    <name>24 **Microchasm (10m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The leftward leaning crack with minimal gear which is best supplemented with pads. Belay off gear at top .  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53354110000" lon="148.87908870000">
    <name>Boulder: Cracked Boulder </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V2/3 ***Cracked Egg (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start crack with hands in the lowest part of it and climb it to the top. A really, really, really nice lowball crack problem!  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V3 *Supermoon (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Stand start with jug and up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V2 *Three-toed skink (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start in crack, follow it right and mantle.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V3 Crystal Surfer (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The grainy slab 5m right of Three-toed skink.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53275428324" lon="148.87984330397">
    <name>Boulder: Arya Boulder </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V0 *Arya (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start matched on large edge. Move to the next large edge then mantle out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53305172786" lon="148.88044227458">
    <name>V3 *Entry traverse (5m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start under roof. then traverse right until you reach the end of the rail on the other side of boulder, then top out.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.537115" lon="148.867465">
    <name>Field: Scattered Boulders </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.53405" lon="148.87487">
    <name>V7 ***Nescient Treehugger (6m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start on good flake. Big moves through slopers avoiding the tree then traverse right through crimpy slots. High mantle to top out.

[ :video_camera: Pete ](https://www.instagram.com/p/CfLGD4cDxnd/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&amp;igshid=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V2 *C1 (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start with left hand fist jam, good edge for the right hand, and right heel hook. Straight up.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 C2 (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start with hand jams straight up. Careful on the hollow stuff at the top. It didn't come off by hand but might be encouraged with leverage.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V0 *C3 (4m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ If you'd like to go for a long walk up the hill there are 4 little corner cracks up there 3 to 4m high. Also nice views of the valley and surrounding tors. Graded to be climbed in decent approach shoes without mats. -35.5334248, 148.8673874  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>VB Rest and Ice (2m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sit start the block underneath 'Injury Denial' and up the right face.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.540178" lon="148.860062">
    <name>V5 **Injury Denial (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Low stand start. Slap up either side before topping out. Large block on left is out  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5051093" lon="148.91492545">
    <name>V1 *Rehab (3m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Sitstart crack left of 'Injury Denial' follow and topout.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.54163590000" lon="148.87009860000">
    <name>Field: Submarine Rocks </name>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.5415733" lon="148.8709537">
    <name>V5 ***Sloth &amp; Avarice (8m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ Approximately 100m south (uphill) of the Submarine is a cave formed by two boulders. S&amp;A traverses the length of the cave following a sharp seam to finish at a an obvious jug. V5 if climbed with feet jammed in the roof, V9 without the roof.

[ :video_camera: Stephen Waring]( https://youtube.com/shorts/nm8ZRyyGfUk?si=sPwtH6gXYQcXEOKr)  ]]></desc>
</wpt>
<wpt lat="-35.541792" lon="148.869883">
    <name>16 **Dave's Climb (20m )</name>
    <desc><![CDATA[ The flake crack 200m south (uphill) from the submarine. Probably the only viable climb amongst the main boulders.  ]]></desc>
</wpt>

</gpx>



